records.addlTxt:
Defendant Courtney Lynn Sims in court.  Attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn in court for Courtney Lynn Sims.  Attorney Jessica Ann Behling in court for State of Wisconsin. 
AS TO THE AMENDED COUNTS 1 and 3: 
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to defendant's plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived their rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

AS TO COUNT 2: Per the plea negotiations and on the State's motion, Court ordered dismissed and read in.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant.
AS TO COUNT 1: 
Defendant sentenced to serve 9  months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count 3. Credit for 5 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 18 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 3: 
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count 1. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 18 MONTHS. 
.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
-provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-Court waived all non-mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges finding the defendant indigent;
-complete an anger management class;
-complete a parenting class;
-AODA assessment and cooperate with any treatment deemed necessary by the probation agent;
-absolute sobriety;
-no corporal punishment of any children.


Appeal rights given. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Copy given to defendant. -- gmb
